[Black "Sidelines 4.h4"]
[Result "*"]

{ In this course we will have an in-depth look at the Cozio Defence, named after Carlo Cozio, Count of Montiglio and Salabue @@StartBracket@@Italy, 1715-1780@@EndBracket@@. After publishing his manuscript Il giuoco degli scacchi in 1766, where he explained the ideas behind 3...Nge7, this line received his name. It all starts with the following moves: }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5
{ The Ruy Lopez remains White's main answer. The abundance of opening theory in the Berlin Defence  3...Nf6  or Morphy Defence  3...a6  can be overwhelming. It can therefore be interesting to surprise the opponent with a line that is much less known. And one that is, perhaps undeservedly so, regarded as dubious. }
3... Nge7
{ The move that this course is all about. Black chooses an unusual way of development but one that does carry some logic. In case White is ever to take on c6, Black will have the option of recapturing with the knight. }
4. h4
{ A hypermodern move! White takes aim at Black's two most likely next moves: Ne7-g6 and g7-g6. It turns out, though, that after White's very committal decision, Black has other options too. }
4... a6
{ Easiest. Before pushing ...d7-d5 Black first gives the bishop a push.   The immediate  4...d5  5.Nxe5  dxe4  6.Qe2  is less clear.   4...Nd4  is decent too and after  5.Nxd4  exd4  6.Qf3  c6  7.Bc4  d5  Black was already doing well in Antipov-Motylev, St Petersburg rapid 2018. @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/ppppnppp/8/1B6/3pP2P/8/PPPP1PP1/RNBQK2R w KQkq - - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.h5!?  c6  7.Be2  is a better option, with approximate equality. }
5. Ba4 d5 6. Nxe5
{ 6.exd5  is likely the better option, but not very testing following  6...Qxd5  7.Nc3  Qd6  with the idea of going ...Bc8-g4 next. }
6... b5
{ The big difference! Having included ...a7-a6 and Bb5-a4, Black can break the pin and obtain an excellent position. }
7. Nxc6 Nxc6 8. Bb3 dxe4
{ Looking at this position, the first thought that comes to mind is what that pawn is doing on h4. }
9. Nc3 Bb7 10. Nxe4 Nd4
{ 10...Qd7!?  with the idea to castle queenside is another very interesting option. Black's compensation is very real. }
11. d3 f5 { Grabbing the initiative. The idea becomes apparent in the line }
12. Ng5 Qe7+ 13. Kf1 O-O-O { With excellent play for the pawn. } *

