11. g3 Qf6 12. f4 { Stopping the advance ...f5-f4. } 12... g5
{ The only move, but a good one. } 13. d4 gxf4 14. Bxf4 Bxf4 15. gxf4 Kh8
{ The point behind Black's 12th move. Now the g-file can be used for counterplay. }
16. Qf3 Rg8+ 17. Kh1
{ Next up is bringing more pieces in. We start to regroup! } 17... Ne7 18. Nd2
Rb8
{ Preparing to bring the bishop to the a8-h1 diagonal by going ...b7-b6 next. }
19. Rg1 b6 20. Rxg8+ Nxg8 21. Nf1 Bb7 22. d5
{ White attempts to keep the diagonal closed but to no avail. } 22... Ne7 23.
Rd1 c6 { Opening up the long diagonal. } 24. Ba4 cxd5 25. Rd4
{ Blocks the ...d5-d4 advance for which Black is craving. } 25... a6 26. Qf2
{ We play the same way after  26.Kg1  ,  26...b5!  27.Bb3  Nc6  and ...d5-d4 next, opening the long diagonal. }
26... b5 27. Bd1 Nc6 28. Rd2 d4
{ Opening the diagonal solves all of Black's issues. } *

