9. O-O Ng6
{ New and, from what I can see, strong.   9...Nd5  10.Qxe4  Bd6  11.d4  O-O  12.Qc2  c5  13.dxc5  Bxc5  14.Nd2  h6  was twice drawn by correspondence player Velker, but I think the text move is more sound. }
10. Qxe4 Be7
{ Black plans to castle and bring the bishop to d5, starting a slow attack. }
11. Bc4
{ In principle, White is happy to exchange pieces. Here though, this operation is not very successful. }
11... Bxc4 12. Qxc4 Ne5
{ Grabbing the chance to jump to d3. It will be very hard for White to play around that octopus. }
13. Qe2 Nd3 14. Na3 { Preparing to kick the knight out with Na3-c2-e1. } 14...
O-O 15. Nc2 Bc5
{ Sealing the advantage. White is not in time to kick the d3-knight. } 16. Ne1
Bxf2+ 17. Rxf2 Rae8 18. Qxd3 Rxe1+ { Wins material. } *

