{ 13...Bd6  14.Ne3  Bf3!!  is a wonderful idea, but on move 14 White can improve with  14.f3  . }
14. Kxg2 Nh4+ 15. Kh1 { Looks like the safer option, but it may not be! } 15...
Qh3 16. Qxc6 Nf3 17. Qxc7
{ This looks like a dead end for Black. The mate on h2 is covered and Qc7-g3 is a huge threat. }
17... Bh4
{ Stopping Qc7-g3 and simply preparing to bring more pieces over with ...Ra8-e8-e6. It turns out White is unable to prevent this plan. }
18. Ne3 Rae8 19. d4 Re7
{ 19...Re6  20.Bc8!  is why Black includes Re7 and Qf4. } 20. Qf4 Re6 21. Bb7
