[White "Chapter 4: Normal Development - 4.0-0"]
[Black "Cozio Defence 4.0-0 g6 5.d3"]
[Result "*"]

{ In this course we will have an in-depth look at the Cozio Defence, named after Carlo Cozio, Count of Montiglio and Salabue @@StartBracket@@Italy, 1715-1780@@EndBracket@@. After publishing his manuscript Il giuoco degli scacchi in 1766, where he explained the ideas behind 3...Nge7, this line received his name. It all starts with the following moves: }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5
{ The Ruy Lopez remains White's main answer. The abundance of opening theory in the Berlin Defence  3...Nf6  or Morphy Defence  3...a6  can be overwhelming. It can therefore be interesting to surprise the opponent with a line that is much less known. And one that is, perhaps undeservedly so, regarded as dubious. }
3... Nge7
{ The move that this course is all about. Black chooses an unusual way of development but one that does carry some logic. In case White is ever to take on c6, Black will have the option of recapturing with the knight. }
4. O-O
{ By far the most popular move in the position, and a logical one obviously. }
4... g6
{ With the knight on e7, the plan to fianchetto the bishop on g7 is the most sensible approach. }
5. d3
{ Not a very critical reply. It allows us to form an ideal setup.   5.Nc3  Bg7  6.d3  will transpose to the note on move  6. }
5... Bg7 6. c3
{ Typical play that we know from these types of positions. The c3-pawn is there to make the c6-knight feel bad.   A look in the database reveals that  6.Nc3  O-O  7.Bg5  is the more popular road, but Black has an easy game here. Simplest is  7...h6  8.Bh4  g5  9.Bg3  d6  followed by ...Ne7-g6 and ideas of ...f7-f5. }
6... O-O 7. Re1 d6 8. Nbd2 h6
{ Before playing ...f7-f5, it makes sense to take control of the g5-square, so as not to get surprised by a combination of Bc4+ and Ng5. }
9. Nf1 f5
{ We can confidently start active operations on the kingside.   If White plays  10.exf5  , I like  10...gxf5  preparing  ...Ne7-g6 and a general initiative on the kingside. My engines assess this position as 0.00 but from a human perspective, I think we are always a bit afraid as White, to see the initiative on the kingside unfolding. }
*

