11. Qxa4 Nxc6 12. Nc3 Ne5
{ 12...Bb7  13.Bf4  would stop ...Nc6-e5, hence we play it immediately. } 13.
Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Be3 Bb7 15. Rad1 Bc6 16. Qc2 f5
{ 16...Re8  , in order to meet  17.f4  with  17...Bxc3  and taking on  e4  , is playable as well. }
17. Bd4 Bxd4 18. Rxd4 fxe4 19. Nxe4 Qe7 { the game is approximately equal. } *

