{ An essential part of Black's strategy, attacking the White centre. } 13. Bg5
h6 14. Bh4 Nac6
{ Postponing ...g6-g5 for now, so as not to allow an exchange on c5 followed by Bd6 in this position.   14...g5  15.Bg3  Nc4   15...Nac6  16.dxc5  dxc5  17.Bd6!  is hard to deal with.  16.b3  Na3  17.Bd3  Nc6  18.Nd5!  Nxd4  19.Nxd4  Bxd4  20.Qh5!  led to a swift win in J.Polgar-Banusz, Warsaw rapid 2011 and is a great example of Polgar's enormous dynamic talent for the game. }
15. d5 Nd4 16. Nxd4 Bxd4 17. Qd2 g5 18. Bg3
{ So far we have been following the correspondence game Muljadi-Jung, ICCF email 2018 and now I propose to deviate with }
18... Ng6 { with great control over the dark squares. } *

