11. Bc2 d6 12. h3
{ White's last move makes sure ...Bc8-g4 isn't a threat anymore. } 12... c5
{ An essential part of Black's strategy, attacking the White centre. } 13. dxc5
{ Often used by White in order to make a draw. } 13... dxc5 14. Qxd8 Rxd8 15.
Be3 Be6
{ The most straightforward. Rather than protecting the pawn, Black sacrifices it for activity.   15...Nb7!?  16.e5  Bf5  as seen in the blindfold game Smeets-Aronian, Nice 2010, is another attempt for Black to keep the game going. }
16. Bxc5 Nec6
{ We'll follow up with ...Na5-c4 on the next turn, with great pressure on the queenside. }
