{ White's last move makes sure ...Bc8-g4 isn't a threat anymore. } 12... c5
{ An essential part of Black's strategy, attacking the White centre. } 13. Bf4
{ A natural developing move, but not one that poses much trouble. } 13... cxd4
{ 13...Nac6  14.dxc5  dxc5  15.Bd6  c4  16.e5  Re8  is not that clear, but I would prefer to avoid it. }
14. Nxd4 Bb7
{ Black developed very smoothly and White already has to be careful not to slip into a worse position. Our next moves are ...Ra8-c8 and ...Na5-c4 with pressure. }
