{ 21...Kh8?!  22.Qxd5  Qe8  23.gxf5  Rxf5  24.Bg4  is probably a bit too much. }
22. gxf5 Rxf5
{ Of White's once proud pawn mass, nothing much is left. In return, we have given up a pawn though, so some questions remain to be answered. }
23. Bg4 { The first move to look at. } 23... c5
{ To illustrate just how sound Black's play is, even  23...Qd7  24.Bxf5  Bxf5  gives excellent compensation given White's weak king. }
24. Qxc5 { 24.Qe3  Rxe5!  is another point behind Black's previous move. }
24... Rc6 25. Qe3 Rxe5 26. Qxe5 Bxg4
{ Engines evaluate the position as even, but from a human viewpoint that is irrelevant. It is clear that Black has great compensation for the exchange. }
