8... Nxh4 9. d3 Bg4
{ 9...Nxg2+  10.Kf1  may just be @@StartBracket@@much@@EndBracket@@ better for White. }
10. f3 Be7 11. Rxh4
{ 11.Nxf7  Nhxf3+!  12.gxf3  Bh4+  is a sequence we will come across more often. Black crashes through on  f3  . }
11... Bxg5 12. Rh1 Bh4+ 13. Kf1 Bd7
{ The position is very unpleasant for White, with the king on f1. } *

