13... Nf4 { With the inclusion of 12...b5 13.Bb3, this move is now fine. } 14.
Bxf4 exf4 15. Nh7 Kd7
{ If you don't know this move, it's going to be hard to find it over the board.   Not  15...Ne6  16.Nxf4!  Qh4  17.Bxe6  Qh1+  18.Ke2  Qf3+  19.Ke1  and Black is lost, since  19...fxe6  20.Rxf8+  Kd7  21.Ng5  Qh1+  22.Kd2!  Qxa1  23.Rxa8  gives White a winning material advantage. As a final note,  23...Qf1  24.e5  Qxf2+  25.Ne2  followed by Ng5-e4, seals the deal. }
