12... exf4 13. Nxc7+ Qxc7 14. fxg4
{ It looks like White is cruising and Black's next move is indeed an important one. }
14... Be7 { Not the first time we see White getting an invite to f7. } 15. Nxf7
f3 { The position is very dangerous for White. } 16. Nxh8 Qg3 17. Qd2 Ne2
{ Blocking the queen on d2, so that a check on g2 is threatened once again. }
18. Qa5 Qg2+ 19. Ke1 Nd4
{ The star move. This is not the time to be materialistic. The king on e1 is what it is all about! }
20. Bb5+ Nc6 21. Bxc6+ bxc6 22. Qxh5+ g6 23. Qxg6+ Kd8 24. Qg8+ Kc7
{ White is without checks and has a huge problem on e2 and h1. } *

